# 📚 Generative AI & Prompt Engineering — Beginner Syllabus

Welcome to your **3-month journey** to learn **Generative AI & Prompt Engineering** — designed for students, freshers, or anyone curious about AI tools and careers.

---

## 📅 **Duration**
**3 Months** (12 Weeks)  
**Time Commitment:** 5–7 hours per week

---

## ✅ **Syllabus Outline**

| Week | Topic | Key Focus |
|------|---------------------------|--------------------------|
| 1 | **Intro to AI & GenAI** | What is AI? What is Generative AI? Real-world examples |
| 2 | **Large Language Models (LLMs)** | GPT, LLaMA, Mistral, how LLMs work |
| 3 | **Popular Tools & Platforms** | OpenAI, Hugging Face, Google Gemini |
| 4 | **Prompt Engineering Basics** | Parts of a prompt, instructions |
| 5 | **Advanced Prompt Techniques** | Chain-of-Thought, system prompts |
| 6 | **Tokens & Temperature** | Controlling output with parameters |
| 7 | **Text-to-Image & Video** | DALL·E, MidJourney, Sora basics |
| 8 | **Build a Custom Chatbot** | Simple chatbot with OpenAI API |
| 9 | **Fine-Tuning Basics** | Hugging Face training demos |
| 10 | **API Integration** | Python + API calls, mini-app |
| 11 | **Ethics & Risks** | Bias, hallucinations, safe use |
| 12 | **Careers & Capstone** | Jobs, portfolio, final project |

---

## ⚙️ **Practical Activities**

- ✅ Experiment with ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini
- ✅ Generate images with DALL·E or MidJourney
- ✅ Use OpenAI Playground for prompt testing
- ✅ Build simple Python API calls with OpenAI
- ✅ Try fine-tuning on Hugging Face
- ✅ Create a personal prompt portfolio

